# Topic Page to Markdown Conversion Prompt

## Your Task
Convert the hardcoded Next.js topic page I'm sharing into a markdown file for dynamic routing.

## Critical Rules - READ CAREFULLY

### 1. Content Preservation
- **DO NOT remove, shorten, or summarize ANY content**
- **DO NOT skip ANY images** - include ALL images from the original file
- **DO NOT change alt text** - copy exact alt text from original
- **DO NOT paraphrase** - keep exact wording from original
- Every paragraph, every image, every section MUST be included

### 2. Image Format
- Use **HTML `<img>` tags**, NOT markdown image syntax
- For image pairs/grids, wrap in `<div>` with inline grid styles
- Format for single image:
```html
<img src="/path/to/image.webp" alt="exact alt text from original" style="width: 100%; margin: 2rem 0;" />
```

- Format for image grid (2 columns):
```html
<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
  <img src="/image1.webp" alt="exact alt text" style="width: 100%;" />
  <img src="/image2.webp" alt="exact alt text" style="width: 100%;" />
</div>
```

### 3. Frontmatter Structure
